<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[227,372,302,328]" box="[227,372,302,328]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,372,302,328]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,372,302,328]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[225,1439,352,718]" box="[272,336,352,378]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[272,336,352,378]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[225,1439,352,718]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Ocelli absent. Antennae probably about as long as forewings (
<typeStatus box="[969,1074,389,415]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">holotype</typeStatus>
antennae incomplete). Scapus about as long as head. Maxillary palps 5-segmented, 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[852,869,426,440]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">nd</superScript>
segment longest, following segments decreasing in length, 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[364,378,464,478]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">rd</superScript>
segment basally barrel-shaped and extended laterad to form pointed spur corresponding in length to 4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[390,403,502,516]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">th</superScript>
and 5 
<superScript attach="left" box="[480,493,502,516]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">th</superScript>
segments. Body and wings light brown. Forewing with length 
<quantity box="[1259,1352,503,529]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
longer than small hindwing. In forewings, apical forks II, III and V present, discoidal cell absent, thyridial cell present, Cu2 running continuously to Cu1b. In hindwings, apical forks I, III and V present (difficult to see, 
<typeStatus box="[281,384,616,642]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">holotype</typeStatus>
forewing hides hindwings in dorsal view). Tibial spur formula 2/2/4. In male genitalia, two-segmented inferior appendages characterized by basally broad coxopodite, tapering and curving mesad. Harpago elongate and tapering continuously towards apex, two-thirds of coxopodite length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
